# Social Caption Generator — Cursor Rules

You are working on **Social Caption Generator**, a Next.js 16 app that turns
product descriptions into platform-native social media captions (Instagram,
TikTok, Pinterest, X/Twitter) using AI.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16.2.1 (App Router) | React 19 | TypeScript 5
- Tailwind CSS 4 | OpenAI SDK 6 (Groq/Ollama/OpenRouter compatible)
- Streaming NDJSON API responses

## Architecture
- `app/page.tsx` — Main client component (form + streaming results)
- `app/api/generate/route.ts` — LLM orchestration (1 brief + 4 parallel captions)
- `app/api/ping/route.ts` — API key validation
- `components/PlatformCard.tsx` — Platform result cards with char counters
- `components/ApiKeyHeader.tsx` — API key management (localStorage)
- `lib/llm.ts` — LLM client factory (multi-provider)
- `lib/types.ts` — Shared TypeScript types

## IMPORTANT: Check Your Inbox
Before starting any work, read `CURSOR_INBOX.md` in the project root.
It contains prioritized task assignments from the project lead, delegated
via Claude Code. Follow the instructions in the highest-priority uncompleted
task. Mark tasks as `[x]` when done and add a brief completion note.

## Code Conventions
- Use the OpenAI SDK pattern from `lib/llm.ts` for all LLM calls
- Stream responses as NDJSON (see `app/api/generate/route.ts`)
- Keep components in `components/`, utilities in `lib/`
- Follow existing Tailwind styling patterns (dark mode support required)
- Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before using any Next.js API
